%% HelixOS — syscall flow (INT 0x80)

sequenceDiagram
    participant App as Caller<br/>(shell or future user prog)
    participant Stub as syscall_dispatch.asm
    participant Disp as syscall_dispatch (C)
    participant Sub as sys_write / sys_read / ...
    participant Drv as relevant driver

    App->>App: load eax=N, ebx,ecx,...=args
    App->>Stub: INT 0x80
    Stub->>Stub: cli, push 0, push 0x80<br/>pusha, save ds<br/>load kernel ds
    Stub->>Disp: call syscall_dispatch(esp)
    Disp->>Disp: bounds-check eax<br/>look up table[eax]
    Disp->>Sub: invoke sys_*(regs)
    Sub->>Drv: kputc / inb / paging_translate / etc.
    Drv-->>Sub: result
    Sub-->>Disp: int32_t rv
    Disp->>Disp: regs->eax = rv
    Disp-->>Stub: return
    Stub->>Stub: restore ds, popa<br/>add esp, 8 (drop int_no/err)<br/>sti, iret
    Stub-->>App: rv lives in eax
